==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Aves
<hw>A"ves</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <ety>[L., pl. of
<ets>avis</ets> bird.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The class of
Vertebrata that includes the birds.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ <xex>Aves</xex>, or birds, have a complete double
circulation, oviparous reproduction, front limbs peculiarly modified as
wings; and they bear feathers. All existing birds have a horny beak,
without teeth; but some Mesozoic fossil birds (Odontornithes) had
conical teeth inserted in both jaws. The principal groups are:
<er>Carinat⟦ae⟧</er>, including all existing flying birds;
<er>Ratit⟦ae⟧</er>, including the ostrich and allies, the apteryx, and
the extinct moas; <er>Odontornithes</er>, or fossil birds with
teeth.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>The ordinary birds are classified largely by the structure of
the beak and feet, which are in direct relation to their habits. See
<er>Beak</er>, <er>Bird</er>, <er>Odontonithes</er>.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Avesta</ent>⟦br⟧
